>\n            A cleaner way for students to pass along appliances, dorm essentials, and everyday goods before they\n            become landfill.\n          </p>\n          <div className=\"button-row hero-actions\">\n            <Link className=\"button\" to=\"/listings\">\n              Explore marketplace\n            </Link>\n            {currentUser ? (\n              <Link className=\"button-secondary\" to=\"/profile\">\n                Open your profile\n              </Link>\n            ) : (\n              <Link className=\"button-secondary\" to=\"/auth\">\n                Create account\n              </Link>\n            )}\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"hero-device reveal-up delay-1\">\n          <div className=\"device-shell\">\n            <div className=\"device-glow\" />\n            <div className=\"device-screen\">\n              <div className=\"device-status\">Student Marketplace</div>\n              <div className=\"device-card featured-card\">\n                <span className=\"tag\">Low waste</span>\n                <strong>Mini fridge</strong>\n                <p>Picked up in Harvard Square instead of thrown out at move-out.</p>\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"device-grid\">\n                <div className=\"device-card\">\n                  <span className=\"mini-label\">School</span>\n                  <strong>Harvard</strong>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"device-card\">\n                  <span className=\"mini-label\">Region</span>\n                  <strong>Greater Boston</strong>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"device-card wide\">\n                  <span className=\"mini-label\">Mission</span>\n                  <strong>Less food waste. Less appliance waste. More reuse.</strong>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </section>\n\n      <section className=\"story-intro reveal-up delay-2\">\n        <span className=\"eyebrow\">Why it matters</span>\n        <h2 className=\"section-title\">A marketplace with a nonprofit mindset.</h2>\n        <p className=\"lede narrow\">\n          When students move quickly, usable microwaves, fridges, storage bins, cookware, and unopened food often get\n          left behind. This platform reframes resale as waste prevention, access, and campus education.\n        </p>\n      </section>\n\n      <section className=\"impact-grid\">\n        <article className=\"impact-panel reveal-up\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Food waste</span>\n          <h3>Leftover groceries can become shared resources.</h3>\n          <p>\n            End-of-semester transitions often leave students with unopened pantry items, meal supplies, and kitchen\n            basics they cannot carry home. A local exchange culture can keep those resources in use.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n        <article className=\"impact-panel reveal-up delay-1\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Appliance waste</span>\n          <h3>Small appliances should not become disposable.</h3>\n          <p>\n            Mini fridges, lamps, fans, kettles, and microwaves are expensive to replace and costly to discard. Extending\n            their life by even one more year materially reduces waste and student spending.\n          </p>\n        </article>\n      </section>\n\n      <section className=\"education-band\">\n        <div className=\"education-copy reveal-up\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Educational focus</span>\n          <h2 className=\"section-title\">Teach circular habits at the moment students actually need them.</h2>\n          <p className=\"lede narrow\">\n            The most effective sustainability tools are practical. Instead of abstract messaging, this app makes reuse\n            visible through nearby listings, regional pickup, shared trust, and simple checkout flows that encourage\n            second life ownership.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"education-metrics reveal-up delay-1\">\n          <div className=\"metric-card\">\n            <strong>Reuse first</strong>\n            <span>Default the student decision toward keeping an item in circulation.</span>\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"metric-card\">\n            <strong>Regional pickup</strong>\n            <span>School, region, and neighborhood filters make reuse feel immediate.</span>\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"metric-card\">\n            <strong>Visible impact</strong>\n            <span>Every listing can communicate the value of redirecting waste away from landfills.</span>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </section>\n\n      <section className=\"cta-banner reveal-up\">\n        <span className=\"eyebrow\">Start locally</span>\n        <h2 className=\"section-title\">Built for campus communities that want less waste and lower costs.</h2>\n        <div className=\"button-row\">\n          <Link className=\"button\" to=\"/listings\">\n            Browse available items\n          </Link>\n          <Link className=\"button-secondary\" to=\"/checkout\">\n            View mock checkout\n          </Link>\n        </div>\n      </section>\n    </main>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default Home;\n","import axios from 'axios';\n\nconst API_BASE_URL = 'http://localhost:5001/api';\nconst SESSION_KEY = 'student-marketplace-session';\n\nexport const fetchListings = async (params = {}) => {\n  try {\n    const response = await axios.get(`${API_BASE_URL}/listings`, { params });\n    return response.data;\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Error fetching listings:', error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n};\n\nexport const createListing = async (listingData) => {\n  try {\n    const response = await axios.post(`${API_BASE_URL}/listings`, listingData);\n    return response.data;\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Error creating listing:', error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n};\n\nexport const fetchUserProfile = async (userId) => {\n  try {\n    const response = await axios.get(`${API_BASE_URL}/users/${userId}`);\n    return response.data;\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Error fetching user profile:', error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n};\n\nexport const registerAccount = async (userData) => {\n  try {\n    const response = await axios.post(`${API_BASE_URL}/users`, userData);\n    return response.data;\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Error creating account:', error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n};\n\nexport const loginAccount = async (credentials) => {\n  try {\n    const response = await axios.post(`${API_BASE_URL}/auth/login`, credentials);\n    return response.data;\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Error logging in:', error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n};\n\nexport const getStoredSession = () => {\n  const stored = window.localStorage.getItem(SESSION_KEY);\n  return stored ? JSON.parse(stored) : null;\n};\n\nexport const storeSession = (user) => {\n  window.localStorage.setItem(SESSION_KEY, JSON.stringify(user));\n};\n\nexport const clearSession = () => {\n  window.localStorage.removeItem(SESSION_KEY);\n};\n\nexport const formatPrice = (price) => {\n  return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' }).format(price);\n};\n","import React from 'react';\nimport { Link } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport { formatPrice } from '../utils';\n\nfunction ListingCard({ listing }) {\n  return (\n    <article className=\"listing-card\">\n      {listing.imageData ? (\n        <img className=\"listing-image\" src={listing.imageData} alt={listing.title} />\n      ) : (\n        <div className=\"listing-image listing-image-placeholder\">No photo uploaded</div>\n      )}\n      <div className=\"listing-meta\">\n        <span className=\"tag\">{listing.category}</span>\n        <span className=\"price-pill\">{formatPrice(listing.price)}</span>\n      </div>\n      <h3>{listing.title}</h3>\n      <p className=\"muted\">{listing.description}</p>\n      <div className=\"listing-meta\">\n        <span>{listing.location}</span>\n        <span>{listing.seller ? listing.seller.username : 'Unknown seller'}</span>\n      </div>\n      <p className=\"muted listing-region\">\n        {[listing.school, listing.region, listing.area].filter(Boolean).join(' • ')}\n      </p>\n      <div className=\"button-row listing-actions\">\n        <Link\n          className=\"button\"\n          to={{\n            pathname: '/checkout',\n            state: { listing },\n          }}\n        >\n          Buy now\n        </Link>\n      </div>\n    </article>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default ListingCard;\n","import React, { useEffect, useMemo, useState } from 'react';\nimport { Link } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport ListingCard from '../components/ListingCard';\nimport { createListing, fetchListings } from '../utils';\n\nconst initialForm = {\n  title: '',\n  description: '',\n  price: '',\n  category: 'General',\n  location: '',\n  school: '',\n  region: '',\n  area: '',\n  imageData: '',\n};\n\nfunction Listings({ currentUser }) {\n  const [listings, setListings] = useState([]);\n  const [filters, setFilters] = useState({ q: '', location: '', category: '', school: '', region: '', area: '' });\n  const [form, setForm] = useState(initialForm);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [error, setError] = useState('');\n  const [status, setStatus] = useState('');\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!currentUser) {\n      setForm(initialForm);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setForm((current) => ({\n      ...current,\n      school: current.school || currentUser.school || '',\n      region: current.region || currentUser.region || '',\n      area: current.area || currentUser.area || '',\n    }));\n  }, [currentUser]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    let active = true;\n\n    async function loadListings() {\n      setLoading(true);\n      setError('');\n      try {\n        const data = await fetchListings(filters);\n        if (active) {\n          setListings(data);\n        }\n      } catch (err) {\n        if (active) {\n          setError('Unable to load listings. Start the backend on port 5000.');\n        }\n      } finally {\n        if (active) {\n          setLoading(false);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    loadListings();\n    return () => {\n      active = false;\n    };\n  }, [filters]);\n\n  const listingCountLabel = useMemo(() => {\n    if (loading) {\n      return 'Loading listings...';\n    }\n    return `${listings.length} listing${listings.length === 1 ? '' : 's'} found`;\n  }, [listings.length, loading]);\n\n  async function handleSubmit(event) {\n    event.preventDefault();\n    setStatus('');\n    setError('');\n\n    if (!currentUser) {\n      setError('Create an account or log in before posting a listing.');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      await createListing({\n        ...form,\n        price: Number(form.price),\n        sellerId: currentUser.id,\n      });\n      setForm({\n        ...initialForm,\n        school: currentUser.school || '',\n        region: currentUser.region || '',\n        area: currentUser.area || '',\n      });\n      setStatus('Listing created.');\n      const data = await fetchListings(filters);\n      setListings(data);\n    } catch (err) {\n      setError('Unable to create listing. Check the form fields and backend status.');\n    }\n  }\n\n  function handleImageUpload(event) {\n    const file = event.target.files?.[0];\n\n    if (!file) {\n      setForm((current) => ({ ...current, imageData: '' }));\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const reader = new FileReader();\n    reader.onload = () => {\n      setForm((current) => ({ ...current, imageData: String(reader.result || '') }));\n    };\n    reader.readAsDataURL(file);\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <main className=\"page\">\n      <section className=\"panel section\">\n        <span className=\"eyebrow\">Marketplace feed</span>\n        <h2 className=\"section-title\">Listings</h2>\n        <p className=\"muted\">{listingCountLabel}</p>\n        <div className=\"toolbar\">\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"search\">Search</label>\n            <input\n              id=\"search\"\n              value={filters.q}\n              onChange={(event) => setFilters((current) => ({ ...current, q: event.target.value }))}\n              placeholder=\"fridge, lamp, textbook\"\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"location\">Location</label>\n            <input\n              id=\"location\"\n              value={filters.location}\n              onChange={(event) => setFilters((current) => ({ ...current, location: event.target.value }))}\n              placeholder=\"Cambridge\"\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"category\">Category</label>\n            <select\n              id=\"category\"\n              value={filters.category}\n              onChange={(event) => setFilters((current) => ({ ...current, category: event.target.value }))}\n            >\n              <option value=\"\">All categories</option>\n              <option value=\"Appliances\">Appliances</option>\n              <option value=\"Furniture\">Furniture</option>\n              <option value=\"General\">General</option>\n            </select>\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"school\">School</label>\n            <input\n              id=\"school\"\n              value={filters.school}\n              onChange={(event) => setFilters((current) => ({ ...current, school: event.target.value }))}\n              placeholder=\"Harvard University\"\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"region\">Region</label>\n            <input\n              id=\"region\"\n              value={filters.region}\n              onChange={(event) => setFilters((current) => ({ ...current, region: event.target.value }))}\n              placeholder=\"Greater Boston\"\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"area\">General area</label>\n            <input\n              id=\"area\"\n              value={filters.area}\n              onChange={(event) => setFilters((current) => ({ ...current, area: event.target.value }))}\n              placeholder=\"Harvard Square\"\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"button-row\">\n            <button\n              className=\"button-secondary\"\n              type=\"button\"\n              onClick={() => setFilters({ q: '', location: '', category: '', school: '', region: '', area: '' })}\n            >\n              Reset filters\n            </button>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        {error ? <div className=\"status error\">{error}</div> : null}\n        {status ? <div className=\"status success\">{status}</div> : null}\n\n        <div className=\"cards\" style={{ marginTop: 20 }}>\n          {!loading && listings.length === 0 ? (\n            <div className=\"empty-state\">No listings match the current filters.</div>\n          ) : null}\n          {listings.map((listing) => (\n            <ListingCard key={listing.id} listing={listing} />\n          ))}\n        </div>\n      </section>\n\n      <section className=\"panel section\">\n        <span className=\"eyebrow\">Create listing</span>\n        <h2 className=\"section-title\">Post something for sale</h2>\n        {!currentUser ? (\n          <div className=\"status error\">\n            You need an account to post. <Link to=\"/auth\">Create one or log in here.</Link>\n          </div>\n        ) : null}\n        <form className=\"form-grid\" onSubmit={handleSubmit}>\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"title\">Title</label>\n            <input\n              id=\"title\"\n              value={form.title}\n              onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, title: event.target.value }))}\n              required\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"field\">\n            <label htmlFor=\"description\">Description</label>\n            <textarea\n              id=\"description\"\n              value={form.description}\n              onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, description: event.target.value }))}\n              required\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"toolbar\">\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"price\">Price</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"price\"\n                type=\"number\"\n                min=\"0\"\n                step=\"0.01\"\n                value={form.price}\n                onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, price: event.target.value }))}\n                required\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"form-category\">Category</label>\n              <select\n                id=\"form-category\"\n                value={form.category}\n                onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, category: event.target.value }))}\n              >\n                <option value=\"General\">General</option>\n                <option value=\"Appliances\">Appliances</option>\n                <option value=\"Furniture\">Furniture</option>\n              </select>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"form-location\">Location</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"form-location\"\n                value={form.location}\n                onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, location: event.target.value }))}\n                required\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"form-school\">School</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"form-school\"\n                value={form.school}\n                onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, school: event.target.value }))}\n                placeholder=\"Your school\"\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"form-region\">Region</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"form-region\"\n                value={form.region}\n                onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, region: event.target.value }))}\n                placeholder=\"Your region\"\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"form-area\">General area</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"form-area\"\n                value={form.area}\n                onChange={(event) => setForm((current) => ({ ...current, area: event.target.value }))}\n                placeholder=\"Neighborhood or square\"\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"form-image\">Photo</label>\n              <input id=\"form-image\" type=\"file\" accept=\"image/*\" onChange={handleImageUpload} />\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          {form.imageData ? <img className=\"listing-preview\" src={form.imageData} alt=\"Listing preview\" /> : null}\n          <div className=\"button-row\">\n            <button className=\"button\" type=\"submit\" disabled={!currentUser}>\n              Publish listing\n            </button>\n          </div>\n        </form>\n      </section>\n    </main>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default Listings;\n","import React, { useEffect, useState } from 'react';\nimport { Link } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport ListingCard from '../components/ListingCard';\nimport { fetchUserProfile } from '../utils';\n\nfunction UserProfile({ currentUser }) {\n  const [profile, setProfile] = useState(null);\n  const [error, setError] = useState('');\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!currentUser) {\n      setProfile(null);\n      setError('');\n      return undefined;\n    }\n\n    let active = true;\n\n    async function loadProfile() {\n      try {\n        const data = await fetchUserProfile(currentUser.id);\n        if (active) {\n          setProfile(data);\n        }\n      } catch (err) {\n        if (active) {\n          setError('Unable to load the demo profile. Start the backend on port 5000.');\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    loadProfile();\n    return () => {\n      active = false;\n    };\n  }, [currentUser]);\n\n  return (\n    <main className=\"page\">\n      <section className=\"panel section\">\n        <span className=\"eyebrow\">Seller profile</span>\n        <h2 className=\"section-title\">Profile</h2>\n        {!currentUser ? (\n          <div className=\"status error\">\n            Sign in first to see your profile. <Link to=\"/auth\">Go to login.</Link>\n          </div>\n        ) : null}\n        {error ? <div className=\"status error\">{error}</div> : null}\n        {currentUser && !profile ? (\n          <p className=\"muted\">Loading profile...</p>\n        ) : profile ? (\n          <div className=\"profile-grid\">\n            <div>\n              <h3>{profile.username}</h3>\n              <p className=\"muted\">{profile.email}</p>\n              <p>{profile.bio || 'No bio provided.'}</p>\n              <span className=\"tag\">{profile.campus || 'Campus not set'}</span>\n              <div className=\"profile-details\">\n                <span className=\"tag\">{profile.school || 'School not set'}</span>\n                <span className=\"tag\">{profile.region || 'Region not set'}</span>\n                <span className=\"tag\">{profile.area || 'Area not set'}</span>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n              <h3>Active listings</h3>\n              <div className=\"cards\">\n                {profile.listings.length === 0 ? (\n                  <div className=\"empty-state\">This seller has no active listings.</div>\n                ) : (\n                  profile.listings.map((listing) => <ListingCard key={listing.id} listing={listing} />)\n                )}\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        ) : null}\n      </section>\n    </main>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default UserProfile;\n","import React, { useState } from 'react';\nimport { useHistory } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport { loginAccount, registerAccount, storeSession } from '../utils';\n\nconst initialLogin = {\n  email: '',\n  password: '',\n};\n\nconst initialSignup = {\n  username: '',\n  email: '',\n  password: '',\n  school: '',\n  region: '',\n  area: '',\n  campus: '',\n  bio: '',\n};\n\nfunction Auth({ onLogin }) {\n  const history = useHistory();\n  const [loginForm, setLoginForm] = useState(initialLogin);\n  const [signupForm, setSignupForm] = useState(initialSignup);\n  const [loginError, setLoginError] = useState('');\n  const [signupError, setSignupError] = useState('');\n  const [signupStatus, setSignupStatus] = useState('');\n\n  async function handleLogin(event) {\n    event.preventDefault();\n    setLoginError('');\n\n    try {\n      const user = await loginAccount(loginForm);\n      storeSession(user);\n      onLogin(user);\n      history.push('/listings');\n    } catch (error) {\n      setLoginError(error.response?.data?.message || 'Unable to log in.');\n    }\n  }\n\n  async function handleSignup(event) {\n    event.preventDefault();\n    setSignupError('');\n    setSignupStatus('');\n\n    try {\n      const user = await registerAccount(signupForm);\n      storeSession(user);\n      onLogin(user);\n      setSignupForm(initialSignup);\n      setSignupStatus('Account created. You are now signed in.');\n      history.push('/profile');\n    } catch (error) {\n      setSignupError(error.response?.data?.message || 'Unable to create account.');\n    }\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <main className=\"page\">\n      <section className=\"auth-grid\">\n        <div className=\"panel section\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Login</span>\n          <h2 className=\"section-title\">Sign in</h2>\n          <form className=\"form-grid\" onSubmit={handleLogin}>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"login-email\">Email</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"login-email\"\n                type=\"email\"\n                value={loginForm.email}\n                onChange={(event) => setLoginForm((current) => ({ ...current, email: event.target.value }))}\n                required\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"login-password\">Password</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"login-password\"\n                type=\"password\"\n                value={loginForm.password}\n                onChange={(event) => setLoginForm((current) => ({ ...current, password: event.target.value }))}\n                required\n              />\n            </div>\n            {loginError ? <div className=\"status error\">{loginError}</div> : null}\n            <div className=\"button-row\">\n              <button className=\"button\" type=\"submit\">\n                Sign in\n              </button>\n            </div>\n          </form>\n        </div>\n\n        <div className=\"panel section\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Create account</span>\n          <h2 className=\"section-title\">Join your local campus market</h2>\n          <form className=\"form-grid\" onSubmit={handleSignup}>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"signup-username\">Username</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"signup-username\"\n                value={signupForm.username}\n                onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, username: event.target.value }))}\n                required\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"signup-email\">Email</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"signup-email\"\n                type=\"email\"\n                value={signupForm.email}\n                onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, email: event.target.value }))}\n                required\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"signup-password\">Password</label>\n              <input\n                id=\"signup-password\"\n                type=\"password\"\n                value={signupForm.password}\n                onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, password: event.target.value }))}\n                required\n              />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"toolbar compact-toolbar\">\n              <div className=\"field\">\n                <label htmlFor=\"signup-school\">School</label>\n                <input\n                  id=\"signup-school\"\n                  value={signupForm.school}\n                  onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, school: event.target.value }))}\n                  placeholder=\"Harvard University\"\n                />\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"field\">\n                <label htmlFor=\"signup-region\">Region</label>\n                <input\n                  id=\"signup-region\"\n                  value={signupForm.region}\n                  onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, region: event.target.value }))}\n                  placeholder=\"Greater Boston\"\n                />\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"field\">\n                <label htmlFor=\"signup-area\">General area</label>\n                <input\n                  id=\"signup-area\"\n                  value={signupForm.area}\n                  onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, area: event.target.value }))}\n                  placeholder=\"Harvard Square\"\n                />\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"field\">\n                <label htmlFor=\"signup-campus\">Campus</label>\n                <input\n                  id=\"signup-campus\"\n                  value={signupForm.campus}\n                  onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, campus: event.target.value }))}\n                  placeholder=\"Harvard Yard\"\n                />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"field\">\n              <label htmlFor=\"signup-bio\">Bio</label>\n              <textarea\n                id=\"signup-bio\"\n                value={signupForm.bio}\n                onChange={(event) => setSignupForm((current) => ({ ...current, bio: event.target.value }))}\n                placeholder=\"What are you selling or looking for?\"\n              />\n            </div>\n            {signupError ? <div className=\"status error\">{signupError}</div> : null}\n            {signupStatus ? <div className=\"status success\">{signupStatus}</div> : null}\n            <div className=\"button-row\">\n              <button className=\"button\" type=\"submit\">\n                Create account\n              </button>\n            </div>\n          </form>\n        </div>\n      </section>\n    </main>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default Auth;\n","import React, { useMemo, useState } from 'react';\nimport { Link, useHistory, useLocation } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport { formatPrice } from '../utils';\n\nfunction Checkout({ currentUser }) {\n  const history = useHistory();\n  const location = useLocation();\n  const [saleComplete, setSaleComplete] = useState(false);\n\n  const listing = useMemo(() => location.state?.listing || null, [location.state]);\n\n  function handleSale() {\n    setSaleComplete(true);\n  }\n\n  if (!listing) {\n    return (\n      <main className=\"page\">\n        <section className=\"panel section\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Checkout</span>\n          <h2 className=\"section-title\">No item selected</h2>\n          <p className=\"muted\">Choose a listing first to enter the mock checkout flow.</p>\n          <div className=\"button-row\">\n            <Link className=\"button\" to=\"/listings\">\n              Back to listings\n            </Link>\n          </div>\n        </section>\n      </main>\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <main className=\"page\">\n      <section className=\"checkout-grid\">\n        <div className=\"panel section\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Checkout</span>\n          <h2 className=\"section-title\">Review your order</h2>\n          {listing.imageData ? (\n            <img className=\"checkout-image\" src={listing.imageData} alt={listing.title} />\n          ) : (\n            <div className=\"listing-image listing-image-placeholder checkout-image\">No photo uploaded</div>\n          )}\n          <div className=\"checkout-summary\">\n            <div>\n              <h3>{listing.title}</h3>\n              <p className=\"muted\">{listing.description}</p>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"checkout-line\">\n              <span>Item price</span>\n              <strong>{formatPrice(listing.price)}</strong>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"checkout-line\">\n              <span>Pickup area</span>\n              <strong>{[listing.school, listing.region, listing.area].filter(Boolean).join(' • ') || listing.location}</strong>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"checkout-line\">\n              <span>Seller</span>\n              <strong>{listing.seller?.username || 'Unknown seller'}</strong>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"checkout-line total\">\n              <span>Total</span>\n              <strong>{formatPrice(listing.price)}</strong>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div className=\"panel section\">\n          <span className=\"eyebrow\">Mock payment</span>\n          <h2 className=\"section-title\">Complete a sample sale</h2>\n          {saleComplete ? (\n            <>\n              <div className=\"status success\">\n                Mock sale completed for {currentUser ? currentUser.username : 'guest buyer'}.\n              </div>\n              <p className=\"muted\">\n                This is a demo checkout only. No real payment was processed and the listing was not removed.\n              </p>\n              <div className=\"button-row\">\n                <button className=\"button\" type=\"button\" onClick={() => history.push('/listings')}>\n                  Return to listings\n                </button>\n                <button className=\"button-secondary\" type=\"button\" onClick={() => history.push('/profile')}>\n                  View profile\n                </button>\n              </div>\n            </>\n          ) : (\n            <>\n              <div className=\"form-grid\">\n                <div className=\"field\">\n                  <label>Buyer</label>\n                  <input value={currentUser ? currentUser.username : 'Guest checkout'} readOnly />\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"field\">\n                  <label>Delivery method</label>\n                  <input value=\"Campus meetup\" readOnly />\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"field\">\n                  <label>Payment</label>\n                  <input value=\"Mock card ending in 4242\" readOnly />\n                </div>\n              </div>\n              <p className=\"muted\">\n                Use the sale button below to simulate a checkout confirmation screen.\n              </p>\n              <div className=\"button-row\">\n                <button className=\"button\" type=\"button\" onClick={handleSale}>\n                  Confirm sale\n                </button>\n                <Link className=\"button-secondary\" to=\"/listings\">\n                  Cancel\n                </Link>\n              </div>\n            </>\n          )}\n        </div>\n      </section>\n    </main>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default Checkout;\n","import React from 'react';\nimport { Link } from 'react-router-dom';\n\nfunction Header({ currentUser, onLogout }) {\n  return (\n    <header className=\"site-header\">\n      <div className=\"brand-row\">\n        <Link className=\"brand-mark\" to=\"/\">\n          <span className=\"brand-badge\">SM</span>\n          <span>Student Marketplace</span>\n        </Link>\n        <nav className=\"nav-links\">\n          <Link to=\"/\">Home</Link>\n          <Link to=\"/listings\">Listings</Link>\n          <Link to=\"/profile\">Profile</Link>\n          {currentUser ? (\n            <button className=\"nav-button\" type=\"button\" onClick={onLogout}>\n              Log out\n            </button>\n          ) : (\n            <Link to=\"/auth\">Login</Link>\n          )}\n        </nav>\n      </div>\n    </header>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default Header;\n","import React from 'react';\n\nfunction Footer() {\n  return (\n    <footer className=\"site-footer\">\n      <div className=\"panel section\">\n        <strong>Student Marketplace</strong>\n        <p className=\"muted\">\n          Buy, sell, and clear out dorm rooms before move-out without leaving campus.\n        </p>\n      </div>\n    </footer>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default Footer;\n","import React, { useState } from 'react';\nimport { BrowserRouter as Router, Route, Switch } from 'react-router-dom';\nimport Home from './pages/Home';\nimport Listings from './pages/Listings';\nimport UserProfile from './pages/UserProfile';\nimport Auth from './pages/Auth';\nimport Checkout from './pages/Checkout';\nimport Header from './components/Header';\nimport Footer from './components/Footer';\nimport { clearSession, getStoredSession } from './utils';\n\nfunction App() {\n  const [currentUser, setCurrentUser] = useState(() => getStoredSession());\n\n  function handleLogout() {\n    clearSession();\n    setCurrentUser(null);\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <Router>\n      <div className=\"app-shell\">\n        <Header currentUser={currentUser} onLogout={handleLogout} />\n        <Switch>\n          <Route path=\"/\" exact>\n            <Home currentUser={currentUser} />\n          </Route>\n          <Route path=\"/listings\">\n            <Listings currentUser={currentUser} />\n          </Route>\n          <Route path=\"/profile\">\n            <UserProfile currentUser={currentUser} />\n          </Route>\n          <Route path=\"/auth\">\n            <Auth onLogin={setCurrentUser} />\n          </Route>\n          <Route path=\"/checkout\">\n            <Checkout currentUser={currentUser} />\n          </Route>\n        </Switch>\n        <Footer />\n      </div>\n    </Router>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default App;\n","import React from 'react';\nimport ReactDOM from 'react-dom';\nimport App from './App';\nimport './styles.css';\n\nReactDOM.render(\n  <React.StrictMode>\n    <App />\n  </React.StrictMode>,\n  document.getElementById('root')\n);\n"]}}